page.title: 19HOUSING and POPULATION
page.content: {HOUSING}Most houses were built at the start of}this century with some three or four being built more recently. There are 8 tennanted properties (mostly agricultural) and the rest of the properties are in private ownership. There is one public house "The Woolpack", serving drinks, bar snacks and meals. The Woolpack also has a skittle alley available for hire. Annual rates are payable to Winchester city council. {POPULATION}As of October 1985: MEN 58 WOMEN 63 CHILDREN 39 ------ TOTAL 160 This includes 20 senior citizens and three retired persons.
